  "title": "Digital Marketing Campaign Manager (Up to $6800) #NKA",
  "description": "<p><strong>Location: </strong>Raffles Place<br /></p><p><strong>Duration: </strong>6 months contract<br /></p><p><strong>Working Hours: </strong>Monday – Friday 9am – 6pm <br /></p><p><strong>Salary: </strong>Up to $6800 + 0.5 month bonus<br /></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong><br />You will plan and execute initiatives to drive sales via the agency channels, enabled by data and digital. This role is responsible for transforming the traditional agency channel into a digitally empowered, high-performing sales force that delivers superior customer experiences.</p><ul><li>Plan and executive campaigns to drive data and digital enabled agency sales.</li><li>Operationalise the integration of digital tools, data, and processes into the agency model to accelerate growth.</li><li>Construct seamless customer journey, from targeting to agents -assisted sales </li><li>Execute initiatives to optimize digital platforms for lead generation and sales, including enabling of data and customer insights and digital assets</li><li>Cross-functional partnership with stakeholders to design customer-centric, compliant, and scalable solutions.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>3-5 years of relevant experience in digital marketing, marketing automation or channel management</li><li>Experience in delivering sales growth in insurance, banking, or financial services preferred.</li><li>Knowledge of sales enablement technologies, CRM, and omni-channel sales models.</li><li>Strong data analytics, financial acumen, and commercial judgment.</li><li>Good stakeholder management skills across multiple business units.</li><li>Strong business acumen, good collaboration skills and an effective team player</li></ul><p></p><p>Ally<br />The Outsourcing Team<br />Recruit Express Pte Ltd<br />EA: 99C4599</p>",
